{
  "doc_id": "12947",
  "text": "The biological consequence of this translocation is expression of a chimeric tyrosine kinase protein with potent transforming capability. The fusion protein strongly activates the MAPK1 and the PIK3CA/AKT1 pathways [CITATION_1] . The occurrence of the ETV6-NTRK3 translocation and consequential expression of the oncogene is an initiating event in the genesis of secretory breast cancer [CITATION_2] . The ETV6-NTRK3 translocation is demonstrated either by break-apart or by fusion FISH design. Positive signal patterns have been seen in most secretory breast carcinoma tumour cells using either assay strategy.",
